commit.message:
Improve sticky mode (#368)

* Improve sticky mode

- clear screen in postcmd, which makes any output show up at the top.
  While it becomes "bumpy" then, this is less fragile than capturing
  stdout/stderr.  Fixes https://github.com/pdbpp/pdbpp/issues/122.

- only display as many lines as fit on the screen.
  Fixes https://github.com/pdbpp/pdbpp/issues/221.

- use lru_cache with format_source

commit.message:
Make pdbpp.Pdb.prompt a property (#349)

This is useful for when using e.g.
[ipdb](https://github.com/gotcha/ipdb) / IPython's debugger, where
`prompt = 'ipdb> '` is used to indicate that pdb++ is used on top.
